1
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:41,009
[The Epoch of Miyu]

2
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:43,900
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:48,310
Mr. Ji.

4
00:01:49,229 --> 00:01:52,310
Mr. Feng is the head
of the HSKP Department after all.

5
00:01:52,310 --> 00:01:54,000
Making a decision

6
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:57,039
on his position all by yourself—

7
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:58,840
isn't that a bit too hasty?

8
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,509
Exactly.

9
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:01,430
You should at least

10
00:02:01,510 --> 00:02:03,170
discuss it with Mr. Wei first.

11
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:04,650
So what you're saying is,

12
00:02:04,890 --> 00:02:06,070
the hotel's general manager

13
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:08,800
can't make personnel
decisions independently?

14
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:11,190
Or do you think

15
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:13,610
I should present Mr. Feng's
record of dereliction of duty

16
00:02:13,610 --> 00:02:15,920
directly to the board,

17
00:02:16,570 --> 00:02:18,829
and let Chairman Wei decide personally?

18
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:30,460
Any other opinions?

19
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:39,640
Susan, please ask

20
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:41,990
the HR Department to hire
a new HSKP director as soon as possible.

21
00:02:41,990 --> 00:02:42,990
Okay, Mr. Ji.

22
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,890
Meeting adjourned.

23
00:03:27,850 --> 00:03:29,220
Don't drink in my car.

24
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:33,170
Zhigang, you have to help me.

25
00:03:34,810 --> 00:03:36,050
How many times have I told you?

26
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:38,310
Clean up your mess when you do something.

27
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:39,910
Now that someone's got dirt on you,

28
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:40,910
how can I help you?

29
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:41,860
So...

30
00:03:41,890 --> 00:03:43,470
So you're just going to
let that guy Ji Feng

31
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:44,630
walk all over you?

32
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,680
Stay calm.

33
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:49,890
He couldn't hold back
and went after my people first.

34
00:03:49,890 --> 00:03:52,420
Don't blame me
for being ruthless from now on.

35
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:55,579
I've arranged for you
to work at a friend's hotel.

36
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,700
And as for your sister,

37
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,650
you know what to say, right?

38
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:15,430
I didn't expect Ji Feng
to be serious this time.

39
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:18,589
Kaixin really took a fall this time.

40
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,769
We both need
to keep a low profile from now on.

41
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,360
Mr. Qian.

42
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:26,510
What's up?

43
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:28,600
Can we talk in private?

44
00:04:30,090 --> 00:04:32,270
Mr. Huang and I have something to discuss.

45
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:33,470
Come back later.

46
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:34,880
Okay.

47
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,870
Isn't she your subordinate?

48
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:41,680
Could she be working for Ji Feng?

49
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:44,830
She works for whoever pays her.

50
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:46,270
My subordinate?

51
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:48,700
She'll just use me and kick me away.

52
00:04:49,370 --> 00:04:51,170
Anyway, be careful.

53
00:04:51,190 --> 00:04:52,920
Don't let her set a trap for you.

54
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:55,830
She wants to play me?

55
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:58,530
She's a bit too green for that.

56
00:05:02,490 --> 00:05:03,160
Come in.

57
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:06,620
Mr. Ji.

58
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,780
You took Marcos to the airport?

59
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:12,630
Yes, I did.

60
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:13,830
Ms. Lu didn't go?

61
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,120
She said she was busy

62
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,920
and asked me to take him instead.

63
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,240
Did Marcos say anything

64
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,120
before he left?

65
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,440
Nothing special,

66
00:05:21,470 --> 00:05:22,810
just some words of thanks.

67
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:24,140
What exactly did he say?

68
00:05:25,270 --> 00:05:26,870
He said our service

69
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:28,510
made him feel at home.

70
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:32,000
He also said he hopes his employees

71
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,720
can enjoy our service too.

72
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,720
Okay. Thanks for your hard work.

73
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,120
Go back and get some rest.

74
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,390
Mr. Qian.

75
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:50,830
Go ahead. What is it?

76
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:52,270
Ms. Lu.

77
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:55,420
Mr. Qian, I'll be straightforward.

78
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,920
I volunteered this time

79
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:58,920
not to suck up to the new leader.

80
00:05:58,920 --> 00:05:59,850
On the contrary,

81
00:06:00,090 --> 00:06:01,950
I did it to test the waters for you.

82
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,800
Ms. Lu, what do you mean?

83
00:06:05,660 --> 00:06:07,420
I know the current situation

84
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:09,050
isn't what you hoped for.

85
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:11,000
But if you want to hold onto

86
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,720
the No.1 spot in sales,

87
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:15,900
someone has to step up
and take on this task.

88
00:06:16,050 --> 00:06:17,360
I'm giving it my all

89
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:19,650
for our sales department's reputation,

90
00:06:19,690 --> 00:06:21,900
not to work for Mr. Ji.

91
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,960
Mr. Qian, please believe me.

92
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:26,970
I'm definitely on your side.

93
00:06:27,050 --> 00:06:28,610
I took the lead in this event

94
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:30,250
just to test the waters for you

95
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:31,840
and see how deep it goes.

96
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:35,060
I would never betray you.

97
00:06:36,790 --> 00:06:38,650
With you explaining it like this,

98
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,140
it actually makes sense, doesn't it?

99
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:43,880
Otherwise, I was starting to think Mr. Wei

100
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:46,430
had sent me an ungrateful wretch.

101
00:06:47,130 --> 00:06:48,360
Mr. Qian, I knew

102
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:50,360
you must have misunderstood me.

103
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:52,630
That's why I hurried over to apologize.

104
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,070
Mr. Qian,

105
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:57,370
I know you like game and wild goods,

106
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,040
so I had someone
custom-order these for you.

107
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,410
Look at you, Ms. Lu.

108
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:01,830
You're too kind.

109
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,040
We're on the same side here.

110
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,720
Here.

111
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,850
Then you should definitely accept it.

112
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,220
Fine.

113
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:11,700
Alright.

114
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:27,170
Seriously,

115
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,890
you never tidy up.

116
00:07:28,910 --> 00:07:30,830
Look at how messy this place is.

117
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,880
We're busy with work,

118
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,430
and have no time to clean up.

119
00:07:35,820 --> 00:07:37,020
What about weekends?

120
00:07:37,370 --> 00:07:38,970
Are you busy on weekends too?

121
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,400
Today's the weekend.

122
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:42,990
Where's Zhenzhen?

123
00:07:43,230 --> 00:07:44,430
She went to the hotel.

124
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:45,840
There's a reception at the hotel.

125
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,900
She had to be there.

126
00:07:49,050 --> 00:07:51,220
I'm not saying she has to do housework.

127
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,750
But she's pregnant

128
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:54,800
and still running around outside.

129
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,680
As a woman,

130
00:07:55,810 --> 00:07:57,810
how much work can she possibly have?

131
00:07:58,140 --> 00:07:59,950
You know her temper.

132
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,130
She can't sit still.

133
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:02,500
She likes to stay busy.

134
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:04,890
If you made her stay home all day,

135
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:06,930
she'd get all anxious

136
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:08,400
and complain nonstop.

137
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:12,140
You can't just indulge her.

138
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:14,460
A woman's pregnancy lasts 10 months,

139
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:16,190
and every single month is critical.

140
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:17,920
She should stay home and rest.

141
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,850
She's carrying our family's child.

142
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,430
You can't be careless.

143
00:08:22,450 --> 00:08:23,570
Understand?

144
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,650
Got it.

145
00:08:26,410 --> 00:08:28,270
You have to take my words to heart.

146
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:29,270
Did you hear me?

147
00:08:29,290 --> 00:08:30,660
Yeah, I hear you.

148
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,789
If it weren't for her

149
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:34,250
being pregnant at that time,

150
00:08:34,250 --> 00:08:36,450
I'd never have let her into this family.

151
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:38,110
Look at her frivolous face.

152
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,960
She won't even stay home on weekends.

153
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,750
Mom,

154
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,550
you know, for a woman,

155
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:47,540
isn't it good that she likes to work?

156
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,360
Besides, I've told you,

157
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:52,550
she has some connections I can use.

158
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:54,710
Why should I go against her?

159
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:56,370
Isn't it better to play along?

160
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:58,690
Don't worry about your grandson.

161
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,450
I will definitely protect him.

162
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,390
You're back.

163
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,200
When did you come back?

164
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:06,910
I didn't hear you.

165
00:09:06,910 --> 00:09:07,820
Just now.

166
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,690
Mom, Yucheng, what are you talking about?

167
00:09:11,060 --> 00:09:11,980
Nothing.

168
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:13,890
I'm helping you tidy up the room.

169
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:14,970
Let me do it.

170
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:16,500
How could I let you clean?

171
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,470
Zhenzhen, you've been busy all day.

172
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:21,100
Go and get some rest.

173
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,450
You don't need to help me.

174
00:09:22,450 --> 00:09:23,920
I'll be done soon.

175
00:09:29,510 --> 00:09:30,320
Mom,

176
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,980
my colleague's looking for me.

177
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:32,900
I have to go.

178
00:09:33,230 --> 00:09:34,180
Sorry I can't stay.

179
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,910
Are you going out to work again?

180
00:09:36,090 --> 00:09:37,240
I got promoted.

181
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,400
My colleagues want to celebrate with me.

182
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,420
You got a promotion?

183
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:41,540
Congratulations.

184
00:09:41,570 --> 00:09:42,700
I'll get going then.

185
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:44,050
Stay safe.

186
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:46,910
Take care on your way.

187
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,630
Look at her.

188
00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:18,120
Hello, Mr. Cheng.

189
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,320
Nice to see you again.

190
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,040
You've got a good memory.

191
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,370
By the way,

192
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:24,660
this is our group's
North China regional head

193
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:25,490
Mr. Dai.

194
00:10:25,970 --> 00:10:26,890
Hello, Mr. Dai.

195
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:27,700
Hello.

196
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,360
I've arranged a room
facing the sun for you.

197
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,370
It has a better view. This way, please.

198
00:10:31,370 --> 00:10:33,490
But he hasn't checked in yet.

199
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:35,560
That's okay.
We can drop off the luggage first.

200
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,600
I'll have an attendant
come up and register later.

201
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,480
Perfect.

202
00:10:38,850 --> 00:10:39,230
Let's go.

203
00:10:39,230 --> 00:10:39,870
Let's go.

204
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:46,000
You can take a rest first.

205
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,200
The attendant will be up
to see you shortly.

206
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,130
Okay, thank you.

207
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,000
Get some rest.

208
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,300
Okay, bye.

209
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:56,080
Mr. Cheng, let me walk you down.

210
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:56,910
Okay.

211
00:10:57,090 --> 00:10:58,000
Thank you so much

212
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,870
for introducing so many guests to us.

213
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:00,720
Rest assured,

214
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,790
our executive floor

215
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:03,790
will wholeheartedly serve them.

216
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,800
I trust you with them, of course.

217
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:07,780
By the way,

218
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,000
is the presidential suite
occupied right now?

219
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,800
We have a long-term guest in one.

220
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,320
But the other presidential suite

221
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:15,120
is vacant.

222
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,070
Whatever you need,

223
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:17,000
just let me know.

224
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,000
Here's the thing.

225
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,910
A friend of mine is Li Bingyan's manager.

226
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,240
Li Bingyan?

227
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:25,090
You mean the actress Li Bingyan?

228
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,370
Exactly.

229
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,080
She's

230
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,120
coming to Shanghai soon
to film a variety show.

231
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,320
Her manager asked me

232
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:32,000
to find a reliable hotel for her.

233
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,370
The requirements: a presidential suite,

234
00:11:34,390 --> 00:11:35,270
and

235
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,750
absolute confidentiality
regarding her schedule.

236
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,910
Her personal life
absolutely cannot be disturbed.

237
00:11:39,910 --> 00:11:40,480
So the first place

238
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,770
I thought of was your Purong Hotel,

239
00:11:41,770 --> 00:11:42,560
and I thought of you.

240
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,680
I wonder if you're willing to take it.

241
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:46,960
Yes, of course we are.

242
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,680
But she's a celebrity

243
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,020
with lots of public attention and fans.

244
00:11:51,020 --> 00:11:53,390
It's bound to come with
a fair amount of trouble.

245
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:55,220
You have to consider the pressure.

246
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:56,220
Don't worry.

247
00:11:56,290 --> 00:11:57,680
We will definitely try our best

248
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:59,280
to meet all her needs.

249
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,920
I'll set up a group chat then.

250
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:01,960
Thank you.

251
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:04,320
Don't mention it. I should thank you

252
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,600
for always introducing such important VIPs

253
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,600
to our hotel.

254
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,060
It's all because of
the service you provide.

255
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:10,720
Please.

256
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:11,510
Please.

257
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:22,440
Ms. Lu.

258
00:12:22,460 --> 00:12:23,220
Ms. Xu,

259
00:12:23,690 --> 00:12:25,290
I need a presidential suite.

260
00:12:25,290 --> 00:12:26,310
The VIP will arrive tomorrow.

261
00:12:26,310 --> 00:12:27,270
Please arrange it as soon as possible.

262
00:12:27,270 --> 00:12:28,200
I'm sorry,

263
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:30,790
but the presidential suites
have just been booked.

264
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:32,270
Then I suggest you figure something out

265
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:33,570
and clear one quickly.

266
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,000
This VIP has an agreement

267
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,030
with our hotel.

268
00:12:36,140 --> 00:12:37,320
The accommodation must

269
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,380
be no less than a presidential suite.

270
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,450
[February 5, 2025]

271
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:43,870
I'm sure you understand who this VIP is.

272
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,590
If we fail to meet the VIP's needs,

273
00:12:46,590 --> 00:12:49,520
will you be responsible
for breaking the agreement?

274
00:12:49,690 --> 00:12:50,750
Whoever it is,

275
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,150
she's indeed a step late.

276
00:12:52,390 --> 00:12:53,320
I'm sorry.

277
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,910
Xu Miyu,

278
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:56,820
why are you working against me?

279
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:58,020
Let me put it this way.

280
00:12:58,020 --> 00:12:59,320
The room she stays in

281
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,920
won't be vacant for the next 2 years.

282
00:13:01,940 --> 00:13:03,420
If this deal falls through

283
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:04,450
because of you,

284
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:06,870
can you afford
to cover the hotel's losses?

285
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:09,670
Don't worry about my personal matters.

286
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:11,910
But what I just said about
the presidential suite situation—

287
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:13,200
that's the truth.

288
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:18,240
Fine.
I won't make things difficult for you.

289
00:13:18,430 --> 00:13:19,920
If Mr. Ji asks about it,

290
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:21,480
explain it to him yourself.

291
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,190
Who does she think she is?

292
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:31,500
[Reception]

293
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Let me check.

294
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:35,260
[Room Status Center]

295
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,030
Come in.

296
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:47,790
Mr. Ji.

297
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:51,080
I have something to discuss with you.

298
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:52,550
Okay.

299
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,200
The Qiao Feifei account

300
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,750
is definitely an opportunity
for our hotel.

301
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:01,750
I won't say

302
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:04,000
how much effort it took me
to secure this order.

303
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,750
And then

304
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,870
Ms. Xu just shuts it down flat.

305
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,840
Does she even have that authority?

306
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:09,440
Alright.

307
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:10,720
I got it.

308
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:13,000
I'll look into the situation first.

309
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,790
Leave this to me.

310
00:14:14,810 --> 00:14:16,860
Sorry to trouble you, Mr. Ji.

311
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:17,800
Not at all.

312
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:23,750
Actually,

313
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,080
I shouldn't bother you

314
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,480
with such a small matter.

315
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,400
But I'm doing this

316
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:30,480
for the benefit of the hotel.

317
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:40,190
If there's nothing else,

318
00:14:40,190 --> 00:14:41,310
get back to work.

319
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:46,360
Okay.

320
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,680
♪Ah♪

321
00:15:06,570 --> 00:15:09,470
♪Talking to myself♪

322
00:15:11,290 --> 00:15:12,590
♪Ah♪

323
00:15:13,220 --> 00:15:17,710
♪Playing pretend
that I've got it together♪

324
00:15:16,170 --> 00:15:17,060
Stop watching.

325
00:15:17,090 --> 00:15:17,910
Hurry up and clean.

326
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:18,950
The guest will be here any minute.

327
00:15:18,950 --> 00:15:21,170
♪ That fleeting moment I tried to hold ♪

328
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:24,860
♪ Let it go when the glass runs dry ♪

329
00:15:22,870 --> 00:15:24,530
Who's this?

330
00:15:25,410 --> 00:15:27,360
You don't know Qiao Feifei?

331
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:28,900
♪ Unfinished longings ♪

332
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:29,520
You've never watched the show Star Maker?

333
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,590
I haven't missed a single episode.

334
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:32,560
♪ Drift like fading embers ♪

335
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:32,220
That's her hit song.

336
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:33,450
The VIP is arriving soon.

337
00:15:33,450 --> 00:15:34,870
How's the cleaning going?

338
00:15:34,340 --> 00:15:36,090
♪ Still longing for yesterday's glow ♪

339
00:15:36,710 --> 00:15:37,500
Almost done.

340
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:39,800
♪ Yet sailing into
the ocean's depths at night ♪

341
00:15:41,010 --> 00:15:43,420
♪ Questions without answers ♪

342
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,690
You two, stop watching.

343
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:44,720
Hurry and clean up.

344
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,250
The guest is arriving soon.

345
00:15:47,310 --> 00:15:48,830
Hurry up, Jia.

346
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:02,960
Thank you.

347
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:08,280
Huanhuan.

348
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,060
Have you seen Ms. Li Bingyan?

349
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,390
I'm here.

350
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:20,670
Hello, Ms. Li.

351
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:22,530
I'm your butler. My surname is Xu.

352
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:25,080
Hello, I'm Li Bingyan.

353
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,120
Your name is Xu Miyu?

354
00:16:29,610 --> 00:16:31,200
It's a really nice name.

355
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:33,150
You don't put on any airs as a star.

356
00:16:34,010 --> 00:16:35,430
I'm not really a star.

357
00:16:35,540 --> 00:16:36,110
Let's go.

358
00:16:36,130 --> 00:16:37,130
This way, please.

359
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:39,280
I'll take it.

360
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:40,760
Thank you.

361
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:53,320
Li Bingyan?

362
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:55,390
Mr. Duan.

363
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:58,800
I... I'm your fan.

364
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,640
You must be Mr. Duan Jr.

365
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:01,900
Hello.

366
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:03,840
You know me?

367
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,960
W-Well, I'm so honored.

368
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,069
Can I have your autograph?

369
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:08,680
Sure.

370
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,660
Well...

371
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,589
Pen.

372
00:17:12,290 --> 00:17:13,819
I don't have a pen, Mr. Duan.

373
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,890
How about a photo?

374
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,099
What a coincidence.

375
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:18,950
I'm sorry.

376
00:17:19,030 --> 00:17:20,920
I'm not wearing makeup today.

377
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,160
It's not convenient to take photos.

378
00:17:24,190 --> 00:17:26,050
Mr. Duan, the guest needs to rest.

379
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,290
I'm sorry.

380
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,600
Where is my room?

381
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:29,610
This way, please.

382
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:30,210
Okay.

383
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:33,830
-We could at least chat.
-Mr. Duan.

384
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:34,900
I'm sorry.

385
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,240
Xu Miyu.

386
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:42,020
I remember you.

387
00:17:44,010 --> 00:17:44,870
Please come in.

388
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,200
This is your room.

389
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,880
If you need anything later,

390
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,960
just call the number on the bedside.

391
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,690
We're at your service anytime.

392
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,020
Thank you for helping me out just now.

393
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,840
I actually have a bit of social anxiety.

394
00:18:16,020 --> 00:18:17,020
I understand.

395
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,210
The more public a figure is,

396
00:18:18,210 --> 00:18:20,070
the more private space they need.

397
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:21,570
Thank you.

398
00:18:22,410 --> 00:18:24,220
You're really sharp.

399
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,100
I'm flattered.

400
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,300
If there's anything I need—

401
00:18:28,590 --> 00:18:29,750
well,

402
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:32,240
I don't sleep very well,

403
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,800
so I'm quite picky about
the living environment.

404
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,680
I'm especially sensitive to noise.

405
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:37,960
We'll keep the hallway
as quiet as possible.

406
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:41,720
Also, I could add some
begonia to your room's diffuser.

407
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,200
Begonia helps
calm the mind and promotes sleep.

408
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:46,400
And having floral scent in the room

409
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,920
will also make you feel relaxed.

410
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,400
Thank you, Ms. Xu.

411
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,510
You seem like

412
00:18:50,510 --> 00:18:52,910
someone who's very considerate of others.

413
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:54,720
Please get some rest.

414
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:55,680
I'll go prepare it right away.

415
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:56,200
Okay.

416
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:17,750
Send the diffuser up now,

417
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:18,680
before the lunch break.

418
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:19,480
Okay.

419
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,160
Here.

420
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,810
Everyone, pay attention.

421
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:25,680
Ms. Li doesn't sleep well,

422
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,030
as I reminded you before.

423
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:28,830
So when we go upstairs to serve,

424
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:29,680
we must keep quiet.

425
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,310
Got it?

426
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:30,900
Yes.

427
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:32,040
Ms. Xu.

428
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:34,240
Ms. Lu is pushing
for the presidential suite again.

429
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,110
Got it.

430
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:41,210
Hello. Is Mr. Duan here?

431
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:42,710
Come in.

432
00:19:46,670 --> 00:19:47,510
Sorry to disturb you, Mr. Duan.

433
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:48,510
I'm Xu Miyu.

434
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:51,640
There's something
I'd like to discuss with you.

435
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,000
We just saw each other.

436
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:54,460
What's there to disturb?

437
00:19:56,090 --> 00:19:56,960
Here's the thing.

438
00:19:56,960 --> 00:19:59,320
Our presidential suites
are fully occupied.

439
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:01,790
And now another VIP wants to check in.

440
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:04,430
So there's a bit of a conflict.

441
00:20:04,450 --> 00:20:05,690
Sounds troublesome.

442
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:07,270
So what do we do?

443
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:10,790
Mr. Duan, that's why I wanted

444
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:12,550
to ask you...

445
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,110
To move out?

446
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:15,920
Not moving out.

447
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:18,000
Just to have you temporarily
stay on the executive floor.

448
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,720
And once this guest leaves,

449
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:20,850
you can move back in.

450
00:20:21,950 --> 00:20:23,880
Then for such a big favor,

451
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,840
how will you repay me?

452
00:20:27,070 --> 00:20:29,240
You're the financial backer
of Purong Hotel.

453
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:31,550
If the hotel's performance is good,

454
00:20:31,570 --> 00:20:32,920
you can also get

455
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,200
a higher return on investment.

456
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,200
Enough.

457
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,200
Drop the corporate talk.

458
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,030
It's boring.

459
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:40,400
Can't you humble yourself a bit
when asking for a favor?

460
00:20:41,650 --> 00:20:43,200
W-Why don't you ask me

461
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,200
what I want?

462
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:46,320
What do you want?

463
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:50,710
Then I have to think about it carefully.

464
00:20:53,780 --> 00:20:55,180
What do you have to offer?

465
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:56,580
I...

466
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:00,960
Hello, Mr. Ji.

467
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:03,510
Where is Ms. Xu?

468
00:21:03,510 --> 00:21:04,400
She's not here.

469
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,530
She's in the presidential suite.

470
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:06,530
Which one?

471
00:21:06,590 --> 00:21:07,790
Mr. Duan's suite.

472
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:09,720
They're discussing the room swap.

473
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:11,000
Okay, thanks.

474
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:15,240
I'm not asking you
to get me the stars from the sky.

475
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,590
Doesn't she just live across the hall?

476
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:17,680
You go knock on her door

477
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,680
and introduce me.

478
00:21:18,910 --> 00:21:20,160
Am I that unpresentable?

479
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,310
I don't mean that, Mr. Duan.

480
00:21:21,310 --> 00:21:22,630
Take a step back.

481
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:24,260
I could knock on her door

482
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:25,540
and recommend myself.

483
00:21:25,630 --> 00:21:27,280
And you're still trying to stop me.

484
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,080
Did she buy you out or something?

485
00:21:29,220 --> 00:21:30,960
The guest across the hall clearly told me

486
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,640
that she didn't want
to be disturbed by anyone.

487
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,960
As her butler,

488
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,480
I...

489
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,220
You really think you're something?

490
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:37,350
You're her butler,

491
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,480
but you're not mine?

492
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:39,640
I don't care.

493
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:42,120
You have to ask her out for me.

494
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:44,140
I'm having dinner with her tonight.

495
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:45,710
I promise you!

496
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:51,670
The knight is here.

497
00:21:51,690 --> 00:21:53,410
We were just having a good chat.

498
00:21:53,410 --> 00:21:55,740
There is a lot to do
on the executive floor.

499
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,650
Tell me if you need anything.

500
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:08,550
Interesting.

501
00:22:08,950 --> 00:22:11,020
[Qiao Feifei, Chinese actress, singer]

502
00:22:11,020 --> 00:22:11,480
[Qiao Feifei, a new-generation
idol female star in China]

503
00:22:11,510 --> 00:22:12,030
[Qiao Feifei's efforts and talent
have enabled her to rise rapidly]

504
00:22:12,050 --> 00:22:12,590
[in the entertainment industry, leading
among the new generation of idols.]

505
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:13,970
[Chinese name Qiao Feifei]
[Alias: Feifei]

506
00:22:17,180 --> 00:22:18,020
Mr. Ji.

507
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:19,960
The presidential suite has been vacated.

508
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,100
Have someone clean it up.

509
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:22,300
That's great, Mr. Ji.

510
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:23,510
How did you get Mr. Duan

511
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:25,170
to move out so quickly?

512
00:22:25,190 --> 00:22:27,760
I gave him a ticket to the fashion gala.

513
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:30,130
He gets to walk the red carpet
with his idol.

514
00:22:30,130 --> 00:22:31,660
Walk the red carpet?

515
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,990
Will Ms. Li cooperate?

516
00:22:34,060 --> 00:22:36,030
That's not my concern.

517
00:22:36,060 --> 00:22:38,190
We'll have to see what he's capable of.

518
00:22:39,130 --> 00:22:40,170
I didn't expect

519
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:42,430
you had such tricks up your sleeve.

520
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,510
Your compliments are the greatest

521
00:22:44,510 --> 00:22:45,510
encouragement for my work.

522
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:46,110
Thank you.

523
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:48,400
Are you playing tricks again?

524
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:52,360
I didn't expect
you held grudges like that.

525
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,380
Mr. Duan.

526
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:15,700
You messed with me?

527
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:17,720
What's wrong, Mr. Duan?

528
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:20,270
Didn't you have a good chat
with Li Bingyan?

529
00:23:20,270 --> 00:23:21,200
Chat?

530
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:23,310
She kicked me away
as soon as she got on the red carpet.

531
00:23:23,310 --> 00:23:24,680
We didn't even say hi.

532
00:23:25,140 --> 00:23:27,580
That's really a pity.

533
00:23:28,460 --> 00:23:29,830
I feel pity for you,

534
00:23:30,230 --> 00:23:32,650
because our cooperation ends here.

535
00:23:32,670 --> 00:23:34,530
I'm telling you I'm very unhappy.

536
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:35,510
Also,

537
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:37,710
compared to the ordinary
leather on this executive floor,

538
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:39,940
I prefer the genuine leather sofa
in my presidential suite.

539
00:23:39,940 --> 00:23:40,880
Mr. Duan,

540
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:43,120
our deal is not over yet.

541
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,240
Do you know

542
00:23:47,270 --> 00:23:48,680
who is currently staying

543
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:49,960
in Room 1816?

544
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:51,750
Who?

545
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,720
Zuo Qiang.

546
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:54,470
You know him?

547
00:23:54,510 --> 00:23:56,350
He's your dad's right-hand man.

548
00:23:56,380 --> 00:23:57,960
Everyone in the circle knows him.

549
00:23:57,960 --> 00:23:59,510
Then... what is he doing here?

550
00:23:59,510 --> 00:24:01,560
We don't know what he's here for.

551
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,690
But now that you've
moved to the executive floor.

552
00:24:03,690 --> 00:24:05,860
Keeping a low profile
certainly won't hurt.

553
00:24:05,860 --> 00:24:06,900
You don't want him

554
00:24:06,930 --> 00:24:08,810
to snitch on you to your dad

555
00:24:08,830 --> 00:24:10,700
that you spend your days
in Purong Hotel's presidential suite

556
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:11,760
having fun, right?

557
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,530
You knew this all along?

558
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:15,890
I just found out.

559
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:21,490
Well, since you're so thoughtful,

560
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:23,820
I won't embarrass you this time.

561
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:26,330
Thank you for your great support.

562
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,970
Don't get too cocky.

563
00:24:34,990 --> 00:24:37,720
We'll have plenty of time
to deal with each other.

564
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,590
Thank you for going easy on me.

565
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,170
Welcome.

566
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:18,230
Welcome.

567
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:27,510
Qingping.

568
00:25:27,570 --> 00:25:30,240
Get two more people down
to help with the luggage.

569
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,570
Stop looking. Let's go.

570
00:25:35,730 --> 00:25:36,940
Wei.

571
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:39,360
You look even more handsome today.

572
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:41,450
Zhenzhen,

573
00:25:41,530 --> 00:25:43,980
I'm only here as a favor to you.

574
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:46,440
You must take good care of our Feifei.

575
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,850
Thank you so much, Wei.

576
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:49,300
Feifei,

577
00:25:49,530 --> 00:25:52,000
you're 100 times prettier
in person than on screen.

578
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,640
Besides, you're a top star

579
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:55,590
and a ratings queen everyone knows.

580
00:25:55,590 --> 00:25:56,830
Our hotel will definitely provide

581
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:58,000
first-class service.

582
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,280
Please rest assured, Wei.

583
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:00,480
Otherwise, Feifei's fans

584
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:02,080
wouldn't let us off the hook.

585
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:03,240
Please.

586
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:08,810
Isn't this the concierge's job?

587
00:26:08,810 --> 00:26:09,310
Ms. Xu,

588
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:11,200
why bringing the luggage over yourself?

589
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,620
Are you a fan too?

590
00:26:12,770 --> 00:26:14,160
There's a lot of luggage
for the presidential suite.

591
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:15,960
The HSKP Department is helping out.

592
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:17,680
Any problem with that, Ms. Lu?

593
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:18,510
No problem at all.

594
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,780
You're quite right.

595
00:26:19,900 --> 00:26:22,110
Helping guests is also your job.

596
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:29,880
Be careful, everyone.

597
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:31,340
Don't bump into anything.

598
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:34,250
You can't afford to pay
for such valuable items.

599
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:39,610
Ms. Xu.

600
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:40,550
Ms. Xu.

601
00:26:41,190 --> 00:26:42,240
Should we book the small banquet hall

602
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,350
or a private dining room for lunch?

603
00:26:43,350 --> 00:26:44,240
The kitchen's asking

604
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:45,490
how many people
they need to prepare food for.

605
00:26:45,490 --> 00:26:47,290
I'll let you know once I confirm.

606
00:26:47,510 --> 00:26:48,270
Ms. Xu,

607
00:26:48,270 --> 00:26:49,960
can you get someone from
the Engineering Department to come over?

608
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:51,110
We need to connect
some external equipment,

609
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:52,550
and check the voltage.

610
00:26:52,550 --> 00:26:53,590
Okay, wait a moment.

611
00:26:53,590 --> 00:26:54,640
Ms. Xu. Ms. Xu.

612
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,180
Can you help me ask
about the number of diners first?

613
00:26:57,180 --> 00:26:58,640
Do you have a piano here?

614
00:26:58,640 --> 00:26:59,390
Ou!

615
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:01,400
Ou, Feifei asked you to go in.

616
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,400
Tell her to wait a moment.

617
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,200
Ms. Xu!

618
00:27:03,570 --> 00:27:05,590
There seems to be a problem
with their credit card.

619
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:06,550
Could you double-check for me?

620
00:27:06,550 --> 00:27:07,750
Is this the right one?

621
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:10,650
Ms. Xu, the guest in the presidential suite
complained about the noise.

622
00:27:10,650 --> 00:27:11,300
Got it.

623
00:27:12,020 --> 00:27:12,990
Ms. Xu, that...

624
00:27:14,660 --> 00:27:16,330
I've heard everyone's questions.

625
00:27:16,330 --> 00:27:17,850
This is a public area.

626
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:19,550
Please don't make loud noises.

627
00:27:19,550 --> 00:27:20,790
There are VIPs resting.

628
00:27:20,790 --> 00:27:22,410
Go back to your rooms and close the doors.

629
00:27:22,410 --> 00:27:23,800
I'll come find you in a moment.

630
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:24,780
You, you, and you,

631
00:27:24,780 --> 00:27:26,170
go wait for me on the executive floor.

632
00:27:26,170 --> 00:27:28,270
I'll come find you
after sorting out the luggage.

633
00:27:28,270 --> 00:27:28,830
Okay?

634
00:27:28,950 --> 00:27:29,270
Okay.

635
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:29,640
Okay.

636
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:30,970
No problem. Dismissed.

637
00:27:31,330 --> 00:27:32,400
Miyu,

638
00:27:32,830 --> 00:27:34,230
I'll go get an autograph.

639
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,490
It's working hours.

640
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:37,590
Sort out the luggage first.

641
00:27:37,590 --> 00:27:39,070
But my idol is right inside.

642
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:41,400
Work first. You'll get your chance later.

643
00:27:43,030 --> 00:27:45,790
Ms. Xu, the presidential suite guests
sent their thanks.

644
00:27:45,790 --> 00:27:46,660
Got it.

645
00:27:49,070 --> 00:27:49,600
Let's go.

646
00:27:51,830 --> 00:27:54,240
Right now, we have two celebrities
staying in the presidential suites.

647
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,770
Qiao Feifei and Li Bingyan.

648
00:27:58,550 --> 00:28:00,030
As public figures, they naturally

649
00:28:00,030 --> 00:28:01,770
have higher demands

650
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:03,310
for privacy and security.

651
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:05,160
I hope everyone will keep this in mind

652
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:06,270
and act accordingly.

653
00:28:06,270 --> 00:28:09,030
Don't wait until their teams
come to complain

654
00:28:09,030 --> 00:28:10,270
before we scramble to respond.

655
00:28:10,270 --> 00:28:11,000
In that case,

656
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,310
it would be beneath Purong Hotel's

657
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:13,270
service standards.

658
00:28:13,270 --> 00:28:14,850
Then what's the best way to handle this?

659
00:28:14,850 --> 00:28:17,050
Should we send more people up to patrol?

660
00:28:17,550 --> 00:28:19,480
The celebrities don't want
to be disturbed in the first place.

661
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,750
Sending more people to wander around

662
00:28:20,750 --> 00:28:22,410
is just asking to be yelled at.

663
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,030
Ms. Xu,

664
00:28:24,510 --> 00:28:26,110
I think the key to this issue

665
00:28:26,110 --> 00:28:27,920
is to resolve the review mechanism

666
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:29,250
on our executive floor.

667
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:31,900
Everyone who takes the elevator
to the presidential suite

668
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:33,560
should be strictly registered.

669
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:34,680
This way, we can manage

670
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:36,330
the flow in and out
of the presidential suite

671
00:28:36,330 --> 00:28:38,460
and ensure
the guests' privacy isn't disturbed.

672
00:28:38,460 --> 00:28:39,640
That's a very good idea.

673
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:42,100
Qingping, I'm putting you
in charge of this.

674
00:28:42,110 --> 00:28:42,790
Okay.

675
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:46,240
Also, if any fans come
looking for the celebrities,

676
00:28:46,270 --> 00:28:47,640
we must remember:

677
00:28:47,660 --> 00:28:49,140
no verbal conflicts

678
00:28:49,170 --> 00:28:50,060
or violent eviction.

679
00:28:50,060 --> 00:28:51,260
We're service staff.

680
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:53,690
Our job is to keep the executive floor

681
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:54,790
and the presidential suite

682
00:28:54,790 --> 00:28:57,090
safe, smooth, and peaceful.

683
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,940
We cannot afford to cause any conflict.

684
00:28:58,940 --> 00:29:00,140
Got it?

685
00:29:00,270 --> 00:29:00,880
Yes.

686
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:01,640
Okay.

687
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:02,570
Get back to work.

688
00:29:10,770 --> 00:29:11,640
As always,

689
00:29:11,710 --> 00:29:13,910
I'll serve you two the Yan Du Xian first.

690
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:26,640
Thank you.

691
00:29:28,550 --> 00:29:29,680
Enjoy your meal.

692
00:29:45,610 --> 00:29:47,030
Is the gluten ball
stuffed with meat ready?

693
00:29:47,030 --> 00:29:47,640
Yes.

694
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:49,290
How much longer
for the shredded pork and ham soup?

695
00:29:49,290 --> 00:29:50,230
Almost done.

696
00:29:52,780 --> 00:29:53,780
Chef,

697
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,600
a lot of tables
are asking for their dishes.

698
00:29:55,600 --> 00:29:56,440
-Got it.
-Thank you.

699
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:57,000
Okay.

700
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:00,580
Where's Chef Yang?

701
00:30:01,170 --> 00:30:02,630
I said, where's Chef Yang?

702
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,170
Chef Yang went to make soup.

703
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,150
Qiaoqi,

704
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:19,270
Ting from the restaurant just told me

705
00:30:19,270 --> 00:30:22,520
that Professor Liu and his wife canceled
their reservation for next week.

706
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:24,180
Was it the food or the service?

707
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:27,810
They said there's a problem
with the taste of the Yan Du Xian.

708
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,440
When did this run out?

709
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,030
I don't know.

710
00:30:55,570 --> 00:30:58,310
Why didn't anyone tell me
we were out of cured pork?

711
00:30:58,310 --> 00:30:59,110
You didn't ask.

712
00:30:59,110 --> 00:31:00,640
What kind of answer is that?

713
00:31:00,660 --> 00:31:02,480
How do you make Yan Du Xian
without cured pork?

714
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:03,160
You...

715
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:06,570
Where's your name tag?
Why aren't you wearing it?

716
00:31:06,570 --> 00:31:08,100
I'm not wearing it. So what?

717
00:31:08,810 --> 00:31:10,600
You never call me by my name anyway.

718
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:11,900
Don't you always call me

719
00:31:11,900 --> 00:31:12,820
"Hey?"

720
00:31:13,260 --> 00:31:14,700
Baozi, say less.

721
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:15,850
Come help me.

722
00:31:17,810 --> 00:31:18,990
Stop looking.

723
00:31:19,010 --> 00:31:20,140
Get back to cooking.

724
00:31:21,590 --> 00:31:22,270
Eight-Treasure Duck!

725
00:31:22,270 --> 00:31:23,070
Four Joy Meatballs!

726
00:31:23,070 --> 00:31:25,310
Braised Pork Intestines and Yan Du Xian!

727
00:31:25,310 --> 00:31:26,720
Yan Du Xian again.

728
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,160
Use

729
00:31:29,430 --> 00:31:30,760
air-dried pork for now.

730
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:32,270
Okay.

731
00:31:44,750 --> 00:31:47,160
Excuse me, what meat is this?

732
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:48,610
Air-dried pork.

733
00:31:49,550 --> 00:31:52,270
And what season
is the air-dried pork meant for?

734
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,470
Summer.

735
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,480
So you use summer air-dried pork,

736
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:59,510
mix in some leftover autumn ham scraps,

737
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,070
and slap together

738
00:32:01,310 --> 00:32:03,170
a half-decent spring Yan Du Xian.

739
00:32:03,850 --> 00:32:05,160
Is your Purong Hotel

740
00:32:05,190 --> 00:32:07,310
trying to ruin its own name?

741
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:11,470
Don't our loyal customers' palates

742
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:14,160
deserve a little more effort from you?

743
00:32:15,870 --> 00:32:17,030
I'm sorry, sir.

744
00:32:17,050 --> 00:32:18,450
It's my responsibility.

745
00:32:24,730 --> 00:32:27,430
[Soups] [Bamboo shoot soup
with fresh and pickled streaky pork]

746
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:29,090
When did the cured pork supply run out?

747
00:32:29,090 --> 00:32:29,960
Last week.

748
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:33,000
They made it clear
they only work with Chef Jia.

749
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:35,410
But I'm already looking for new suppliers.

750
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:37,300
Please give me a little more time.

751
00:32:38,070 --> 00:32:39,680
It will be difficult
during this special period,

752
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:41,690
but please hang in there, Chef Li.

753
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:42,510
I have faith in you.

754
00:32:42,510 --> 00:32:44,040
I won't let you down, Mr. Ji.

755
00:32:44,530 --> 00:32:47,330
We absolutely cannot
let our signature dish fail.

756
00:32:49,550 --> 00:32:52,150
Let me know
when there's something good to eat.

757
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:53,530
You got it.

758
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:17,520
Xu Miyu!

759
00:34:20,340 --> 00:34:21,870
Where are you going so late?

760
00:34:21,920 --> 00:34:23,179
I'm going to the hotel.

761
00:34:23,510 --> 00:34:25,179
There's something I need to do.

762
00:34:25,179 --> 00:34:26,310
Is everything okay?

763
00:34:29,239 --> 00:34:33,949
[Bund Tunnel]

764
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:38,719
You're here.

765
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:41,949
[Staff Only]

766
00:34:39,670 --> 00:34:41,810
How is it? Smells good, right?

767
00:34:42,270 --> 00:34:44,270
Makes your mouth water, doesn't it?

768
00:34:46,750 --> 00:34:47,790
Miyu...

769
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,679
You scared me.

770
00:34:49,699 --> 00:34:50,739
Why is it you?

771
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,230
I saw the light in the kitchen.

772
00:34:52,230 --> 00:34:52,760
So I came to check.

773
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:54,420
Why haven't you left work yet?

774
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,760
Where did you get the cured pork?

775
00:35:02,170 --> 00:35:03,170
Smells so good.

776
00:35:05,250 --> 00:35:06,910
Let me taste it for the guests.

777
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,380
Is it for you?

778
00:35:09,580 --> 00:35:11,170
-Qiaoqi.
-Then who's it for?

779
00:35:11,170 --> 00:35:11,920
You're here.

780
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,650
You invited Xu Miyu?

781
00:35:14,220 --> 00:35:15,950
Let's both try it. You go first.

782
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,530
Why are you here?

783
00:35:21,030 --> 00:35:21,880
Mr. Ji.

784
00:35:22,070 --> 00:35:24,190
Did you invite Mr. Ji?

785
00:35:24,230 --> 00:35:24,930
No, no.

786
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:26,720
We ran into each other on the way.

787
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:29,720
Didn't I tell you to let me know
when there's good food?

788
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:31,330
This is just a test.

789
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:32,590
I don't know how it will turn out.

790
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:34,520
So I wanted Miyu to help me check it.

791
00:35:35,510 --> 00:35:37,000
As an experienced foodie,

792
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:38,610
I can help with that too.

793
00:35:38,630 --> 00:35:39,670
So can I.

794
00:35:42,180 --> 00:35:43,510
Then let's all try it.

795
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:46,590
It smells so good.

796
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:54,920
Earthy from the clay pot,
a hint of charcoal,

797
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,830
with a little bit of smokiness.

798
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:59,150
Tomorrow we can use this Yan Du Xian

799
00:35:59,150 --> 00:36:00,510
to blow the diners away.

800
00:36:00,870 --> 00:36:02,190
It can definitely become our

801
00:36:02,190 --> 00:36:04,070
new signature dish at Purong Hotel.

802
00:36:04,070 --> 00:36:05,510
Keep bragging.

803
00:36:05,550 --> 00:36:08,010
It's not up to you
whether the guests like it.

804
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:09,740
I'm really not confident.

805
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:11,510
After all, Chef Jia's Yan Du Xian

806
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:13,000
dominates Shanghai.

807
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:15,570
Many guests come here for its reputation.

808
00:36:17,030 --> 00:36:19,480
Will the Chinese restaurant
really be ruined in my hands?

809
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:22,560
The quality of Yan Du Xian
must certainly continue to improve.

810
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:24,070
But does it have to be exactly the same

811
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:25,070
as Chef Jia's?

812
00:36:25,310 --> 00:36:26,310
I don't think so.

813
00:36:26,590 --> 00:36:27,320
Times change,

814
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:28,960
and so do diners' tastes.

815
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:31,000
Now that Chef Jia has blocked

816
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:31,880
all supply channels,

817
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:33,510
we can find another way.

818
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:34,670
Let's see if there

819
00:36:34,860 --> 00:36:36,630
are other possibilities for this dish.

820
00:36:36,630 --> 00:36:37,470
Okay, Mr. Ji.

821
00:36:37,510 --> 00:36:38,760
Tomorrow, I'll keep looking

822
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:40,230
for cured pork suppliers.

823
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:43,240
I'll help you.

824
00:36:43,510 --> 00:36:44,510
There are plenty of

825
00:36:44,510 --> 00:36:47,140
cured pork makers
in the Yangtze River Delta.

826
00:36:47,170 --> 00:36:49,290
We can definitely find a good source.

827
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:50,960
Leave it to me.

828
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,510
Stop bragging.

829
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:54,670
It'd be great
if you don't make things worse.

830
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:55,510
See?

831
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:58,360
You always put me down.

832
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:03,030
One last bowl.

833
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:15,780
Yan Du Xian.

834
00:37:16,690 --> 00:37:17,810
Please enjoy.

835
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,070
Hello?

836
00:37:24,540 --> 00:37:25,190
Okay.

837
00:37:25,210 --> 00:37:26,270
I'll be right back.

838
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:42,310
Waiter, I'd like to order!

839
00:37:47,190 --> 00:37:47,960
Hello, sir.

840
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,120
What would you like to eat?

841
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:50,680
One Yan Du Xian.

842
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,880
Anything else, sir?

843
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:53,670
No, thanks.

844
00:38:04,700 --> 00:38:05,840
[Trending]

